{
    "name": "Account Returns Due ",
     "content": "Good Evening <b>#NAME#</b><br><br>We would like to update you that the Annual Accounts for the period <b>#PERIOD#</b> are due on<b>#DUEON#</b>. In order to prepare the Annual Accounts we would require the following documentation:<br><br>1. Bank statements (csv format)<br>Please note, there will be an additional charge if bank statement will not be provided in excel format. If there are any problems with downloading this format, please contact us for further instruction.<br><br>2. List of any addition of assets value and invoices paid personally,<br><br>3. Income Invoices,<br><br>4. Cheque books (counter part) if used,<br><br> 5. List of all your business expenses including invoices (paid both by cash and from bank),<br><br> 6. Mileage log.<br><br> Bank statements and sales invoices can be sent via e-mail.<br><br> Expenses invoices, bills and receipts can be hand delivered or posted to our office directly at the address below:<br><b>#COMPANYADDRESS#</b><br><br>If company did not trade and was dormant we will need written confirmation to finalize submission. Cost of dormant submission is <b>250</b> . That includes submission of confirmation statement, annual account, corporation tax and nil director s tax return.<br><br> If we prepare VAT returns for your company and the documents are delivered to us on a quarterly basis, then please ignore this email as we will only contact you if there is any need for additional information.<br><br> Please arrange to deliver the documents by <b>#DOCUMENTSSENTBY#</b> to ensure on time submission.In the event of failure to provide the above-mentioned documents within the requested deadline, the company accounts may not be submitted on time which may result in financial penalties being imposed for which Acumen+ will not accept any responsibility.<br><br> Please note that if the documents will be provided within the last month of submission deadline, there will be an extra charge of <b>150</b>.<br><br><br> Please also update us on any other income received personally (excluding from your company),<br>such as rental income, interest received, etc, which we should be aware of, in order to prepare your personal tax return for tax year #TAXDATES#.<br><br> If you have any queries please do not hesitate to contact me.<br><br> Kind regards<br><br>Regards<br><br> Annual Accounts Team<p>#COMPANYADDRESS#</p>"
   
}
